inn1.comm: And what a start! Kemar Roach's first ball is an inswinging yorker that crashes into offstump, Watson looks shocked at receiving that cracker first up
another attempted yorker, this one is a low full toss on middle stump, Ponting shuffles across and flicks it to fine leg
Paine is also off the mark by pushing a full ball outside off towards cover
Roach keeps it up to the batsman, Ponting lunges forward and taps the ball towards extra cover
first short ball from Roach, line is wrong, down the leg side
reverts to a full length, just outside off, punched to mid-off
length ball angling into the pads, tapped towards square leg
stifled appeal for lbw, length ball jags into the batsman, who shoulders arms and is rapped high on the pads, too high to be in danger of being given out
full and wide, mistimed through the covers for a couple of runs
keeping it full, and pretty close to offstump, Ponting pushes it towards mid-off this time
slight inward movement troubles Paine, he gets an inside edge onto the pads
good bounce there, just pitching on a back of a length, no room for Paine to work with, he lets the ball through to the keeper
slightly fuller this time, and wider, Paine gets forward and looks to drive towards extra cover, mistimes it to the leg side
Roach oversteps to give away a free-hit, it was a back of a length on middle and leg, Ponting tucks it towards square leg
quick bouncer that follows Paine, 148.5kmh, he was backing away but got no room to free his arms, he is hit on the gloves, the ball dribbles back towards the  bowler
another bouncer from Roach, Paine defends off the back foot
another no-ball, that was 150.6 kmh, shortish again, Paine defends
this was the slower one from Roach, 108kmh, Paine backs away and slices it over point
length ball just outside off, batsman opens the face to guide the ball towards backward point
Roach is working up some serious pace here, 151.3kmh, fullish ball heading for offstump, Ponting defends off the front foot
a touch shorter this time, line is again close to offstump, Ponting inside-edges the ball towards midwicket, thinks of a single before screaming 'No'
Tonge's formula against Pakistan was to keep it just back of a length, and pegging away at offstump, he sends down on of those again, Paine shoulders arms
slightly fuller, Paine gets on the front foot and punches the ball straight towards mid-off
Paine lunges forward, plays the ball with soft hands, dropping it towards point, and the batsmen zip through for a single
compact forward defensive from Ponting this time
Ponting gets a big stride in and crunches the ball wide of mid-off, Andre Fletcher makes good ground to cut that one off
shortish ball angling down the leg side, Paine comes down the track and tries to whip the ball, gloves it fine, Walton dives to his left to take the pace off that ball
short of length, defended back down the pitch
short and wide, steered towards deep backward point for a single
that nipped into the batsman sharply, strikes the pad but he's safe as that was heading down leg, the ball bobbles toward square leg
length ball, homing in on offstump, defended stoutly back to the bowler
sharp bounce troubles Paine, 149.7kmh, just back of a length and that takes off, strikes the bat near the shoulder
full and just outside off, dug out towards the bowler
overpitched by Tonge, heading towards leg stump, Ponting accepts the gift, whips it to the midwicket boundary, the first of the Australian innings
good-looking shot from Ponting, but cracked straight at cover
Tonge holds the length back a touch and Ponting is rapped high on the pads as he looks to defend
on middle and leg this time, Ponting turns it in front of square leg for a single
Paine is in all sorts of trouble here, back of a length delivery, Paine gets forward and looks awkward as he tries to cover for the inward movement, gets an inside edge onto his thigh pad
outside off this time, left alone by Paine
shortish ball on the leg stump, Ponting is on the backfoot quickly, and just helps it on it's way to the fine leg boundary with a flat bat
151.1kmh, it holds it's line after pitching on a length just outside off, has Ponting feeling for it, beats the batsman
another boundary, full ball on middle and leg, bread and butter for Ponting, flicked behind square for four
a touch shorter, on middle stump, Ponting punches it towards mid-on
this is poor from Roach, his third no-ball, full and outside off, defended towards cover, time for a free-hit
Roach goes for the yorker on legstump, ends up as a half-volley, Ponting gets his front foot out of the way and powers the ball past mid-on
another boundary ends an expensive over, on the pads, that's terrible bowling especially when you have with the fine leg in the circle, thank you says Ponting as he guides it for four past fine leg
length ball on middle and leg, punched towards mid-on for a single
slightly fuller this time, same line, clipped towards midwicket by Paine
that's frustrating for the bowler, nips in sharply off a back of a length, gets the inside edge, but the ball races to the left of the keeper for four
Paine very keen to get on the front foot despite the amount of bounce available on this pitch, he tips this one towards point and gets a quick single
again Tonge gets the ball to rise sharply from a length, Ponting is struck on the thigh pad, the ball rolls towards the square leg
a flamboyant shot from Paine fetches him four, and quite a risky one given the bounce around, he waltzes down the pitch and whips a length ball from outside off towards the square-leg boundary
full and on the pads, pushed towards mid-on
short of length and very wide, at Sammy's pace that is a hit-me delivery, Ponting rocks back and cracks it over extra cover for a boundary
this one moves away a touch after pitching wide of offstump, Ponting shoulders arms
shorter ball this time, again well outside off, and a hint of away movement, Ponting is happy to let this go as well

whoah! that slipped out of Sammy's hands, and loops over the batsman's head on the full, not too much pace as it passed Ponting, so not too much danger involved, unlike Tino Best's full-speed beamer at  Umar Akmal earlier this week
just outside off, Ponting opens the face and glides the ball to third man
a little wider outside off, again Sammy gets the ball to shape away from the batsman, Paine watches it through to the keeper
Tonge gets the ball to duck in from a length, Ponting looks to defend off the front foot, extra bounce as well that time, and Ponting is struck on the stomach
Paine jabs this one towards mid-on
Paine's struggles continue, inddiper from Tonge beats the bat and brushes Paine's trousers on the way to the keeper, muted appeal for caught-behind
length ball on offstump, punched firmly back to the bowler
much shorter this time, nice and tight around off, Paine blocks the ball towards point
again sharp bounce, Paine is having a torrid time here, an ungainly prod at the ball which reaches him at shoulder height, struck on the gloves, to Paine's credit he's surviving this testing time
fullish ball just outside off, turned towards mid-on for a single
dropped, Paine's misery nearly ended there, the away movement gets the outside edge and it was a fairly straightforward take to Chadwick Walton's right, he spills it
length ball, heading for middle and leg, Ponting clips it to midwicket
even Ponting, who has looked in great touch so far, is beaten this time, feeling for the ball outside off, the ball seams away past the bat
another probing delivery to end the over, on a length just outside off, draws Ponting towards it and again he's beaten
slower legcutter, pushed towards the cover
Paine punches that on the up past point for an easy two
slight short, tight around off, opens the face to steer the ball towards third man
on middle stump, Ponting pushes it towards mid-on
full and wide, Ponting looks to lash it past mid-off, gets it on the toe end of his bat, the ball flies in the air towards mid-off, but lands well short of the fielder
back of a length, angling into off, Ponting shuffles across and tucks it behind square leg
Ponting is struck on the knuckles as he looks to defend towards the off side
pushed off the front foot towards extra cover this time
length ball just outside off, Paine gets behind the line and defends it
full and slightly wide outside off, Paine tries to power it through the off side, can't beat the man at short cover
a touch shorter, and closer to offstump, Paine defends towards short cover
back of a length and close to offstump, Paine still manages to gets inside the line and glide it towards backward point
back of a length, angling into offstump, Paine gets forward and defends
short ball, Paine goes for the pull, misses the ball which sails over his shoulder
no missing out on this one, it was a slower ball, fullish on off, Paine muscles it back uppishly past the bowler
back of a length and outside off, Paine walks across his stumps and works the ball behind square leg
length ball just outside off, Ponting lunges forward and pushes it towards cover
Tonge finishes his seventh over with a length ball on middle, Ponting blocks it back down the pitch, a bit of extra bounce in that one, bottom hand comes off the bat as Ponting  defends
on middle and leg, batsman shuffles across and nudges it behind square leg
again Ponting is troubled by Sammy's away movement, he tried to run it to third man but doesn't connect with the ball
Ponting was a bit early into that defensive shot, it was a length ball on middle and off, the ball is in the air for a bit before reaching the bowler
slightly shorter this time, Ponting plays a far more confident forward defensive this time

a ripper from Sammy, this time Ponting is troubled by the extra bounce, mught have hit a crack as that soared off a length, that strikes the bat halfway up the handle, Ponting is surprised and the bat slips out of his hands as he defends
this time Ponting gets forward and blocks the ball towards cover
full ball on the pads, punched towards mid-on

was that a chance? short and very wide,  Paine gets a top edge towards Nikita Miller at third man, it was in the air a long time, Miller stopped running towards the ball, he could have taken a catch if he had, he prefers to hang back to take it on the bounce
a bit of width for Ponting to work with, cracks it towards cover
outside off and Paine leaves it alone
on middle and leg, defended towards square leg
Paine ends the over with a single to third man, all along the ground this time, Ponting was calling for the second, but the batsman wisely decide against it
overpitched on offstump, 123kmh, blocked back to the bowler
very full and outside off, Paine take step out of the crease and forces it towards mid-off
back of a length and wide outside off, Paine carves it away behind a diving point fielder
full and on off stump, Ponting leans across and pushes it towards mid-on, steals a quick single
length ball outside off, steered towards third man by Paine
on the pads, worked away to square leg for another single to end the over
that one shapes in towards Ponting, who keeps bat and pad close together as he defends
back of a length and wide outside off, slashed towards backward point
that was a back of a length angling into Ponting, he was looking to pull that one, but misses and is hit on the thigh pad outside off
this time he connects with the pull, he directs the ball towards fine leg, a little better placement would have fetched him four
punched towards extra cover for a single
full and on offstump, Ponting is squared by as he pushes the ball towards cover
length ball heading for leg stump, jabbed towards mid-on
back of a length, just outside off, holds it's line, Ponting blocks it to the off side
length ball just outside off, Ponting raises his front foot as he cuts stylishly
Paine tries to break the shackles by charging down the track and looking to loft over the bowler's head, doesn't connect
dabs it off the back foot towards third man for a single
overpitched on middle and leg, Ponting pats it back to the bowler

there's the breakthrough West Indies wanted, Bernard's delivery held it's line just outside off, Paine was perhaps looking for Bernard's usual inward movement, gets a fine edge to the keeper, who collects this time
easy leave for him first up, well outside off stump
this one is closer to the stump, Hussey blocks it towards the off side
length ball on middle and off, Hussey pokes it towards the off side and gets a single to get off the mark
Ponting leans across and whips the ball firmly towards the leg side, a diving stop at short midwicket saves West Indies three runs
angling across Hussey who is content to leave that one

that will go down as a six but that could have so easily been a wicket, a short of length ball on the ribs, Ponting swivels and pulls it over fine leg for a six, the fielder there was a few yards in from the rope, if he had hung back that could have been a catch
gets forward and punches it towards extra cover
Ponting reaches a superb half-century with a lovely square drive, it was a half-volley way outside off, Ponting reached across and dispatched it
and this is even better from Ponting, length ball outside off, Ponting eases it past a diving short cover and squeezes it past extra cover for four more
short and on the ribs, nudged towards square leg
on the pads again, clipped to square leg for a single
half-volley well outside off, Hussey drives it square for a single
angling into offstump, Ponting defends back down the pitch
a direct hit, is that out? Ponting leans across and tucks a leg-stump ball to deep midwicket, he scampers back for the second and just makes his ground before the throw breaks the stumps
length ball outside off, pushed towards extra cover
Ponting clips that to midwicket for a single
'Wait there' Hussey shouts after punching the ball towards cover
watchfully defended towards the bowler
Ponting eases this one towards mid-on for an easy single
on middle and leg, turned away behind square leg
gives this one a bit of air, turns away after pitching well outside off to beat Ponting
pushed towards cover with a flat bat
on middle and leg, turned towards midwicket
the batmen waddle through for a single after Ponting taps the ball to long-on
full, and on offstump, Hussey pushes it towards mid-off
Ponting pulls off the front foot, the ball goes on the bounce to deep square leg
nice and tight around offstump, Hussey blocks it towards the off side
another dot ball, Hussey pushes this one towards short cover
back of a length, angling across the batsman, Hussey shoulders arms
a bit of an outside edge towards point, 'Wait' cries Ponting
again Ponting gets forward and blocks the ball towards point
on the pads, worked away behind square leg
Ponting gets on the front foot and punches it to extra cover
length ball turning in after pitching outside off, clipped towards midwicket
all too easy for Australia here, the batsmen jog through for a risk-free single after pushing the ball to long-on
Ponting shuffles across and looks to tucks a middle-stump ball behind square leg, is struck high on the pads
Hussey falls, it was not the greatest of deliveries, shortish and on legstump, Hussey was looking to pull, gets a top edge towards Andre Fletcher at fine leg
an authoritative pull from Ponting to a delivery that wasn't too short, keeps the ball along the ground as well
muscled past extra cover by Ponting
Ponting gets forward and steers the ball towards point
down the leg side, the ball shapes further away from the stumps, the keeper can't collect cleanly
much-better ball to end the over, on a length heading for offstump, defended stoutly back towards the bowler
Ferguson gets forward and defends it towards point
blocked off the backfoot towards the off side
length ball just outside off, blocked towards short cover
short delivery just outside off, cut straight at point
fullish on the pads, worked towards long-on for a single
slightly quicker from Miller, glided towards point
way outside off stump
a yorker from Bernard, strikes the batsman low on the pads but that was heading down leg
another wide outside off, this was a tighter one for the umpire to call than the previous one
length ball on middle and leg, solid forward defensive from Ferguson
overpitched outside off, good looking drive from Ferguson, straight towards short cover
an effortless boundary for Ferguson, he walks across the stumps to flicks a ball from outside off behind square leg for a boundary, wonderfully timed shot, and the lightning outfield helped
overpitched, on middle and leg, hits Ferguson high on the pads, the ball rolls towards square leg
Ponting gets forward and plays the ball with soft hands towards cover
overpitched outside off, driven off the front foot, a diving short cover can't stop that cleanly
blocked towards the off side
a short ball from Miller, batsman rocks back and gets the ball away towards sweeper cover
Ponting looks to sweep, inside-edges onto his pad
dropped towards the off side for a quick single
Ferguson gets a big stride in as he defends towards point
straight away goes to his short-of length, on offstump formula, jabbed towards cover
Ferguson defends that from the crease towards point
shorter and wider from Tonge, cut hard towards point by Ferguson
short and closer to the offstump, Ferguson swivels and pulls that over short midwicket for a boundary
length ball on middle and leg, worked away to deep backward square leg
stands tall and defends towards cover
short ball outside off, cut towards extra cover by Ferguson
Miller keeps it tight around off, defended behind point

Miller has got the big wicket, Ponting is gone, he came down the pitch to drive, was nowhere near the pitch of the ball, which was well flighted, it turns past Ponting's bat and Chadwick Walton whips the bails off
length ball pitching just outside off, White stretched forward to defend
White is off the mark, eases the ball down to long-on
Ferguson is again well forward as he defends the ball outside off
back of length delivery on the stumps, White stands tall and pushes it onto the offside
just back of a length, on middle and leg, defended back to the bowler
shortish ball, jags in sharply after pitching outside off, White is stuck high on the pads
Ferguson chases after a short and wide one, but fails to connect
full delivery, Ferguson looks to drive, gets an outside edge past the keeper for a streaky boundary
'No, no' White shouts as he see Ferguson set off for a single after pushing the ball straight to square leg
back of a length outside off, Ferguson stand tall and defends it
Miller continues to strangle Australia, on middle stump, defended to the leg side
switches to off stump this time, blocked back to the bowler
drops short this time, White backs away and pushes it towards mid-odd
defended back to the bowler
and again, Miller keeps it around off
White defends to the bowler for the third time in a row to complete the maiden
short of length just outside off, carved away to third man
short and very wide, batsman couldn't have reached even if he had tried
angling into middle stump, batsman shuffles across and flicks it down to fine leg
full and just outside off, defended towards mid-off
length ball just outside off, blocked towards cover this time, just wide of the fielder
length ball in middle and leg, defended towards the leg side
the captain Reifer dives full length to cut off a Ferguson drive at short cover
very full, pitching on middle, driven inside out towards mid-off
on middle and off, Ferguson keeps bat and pad together as he defends
length ball, pitching just outside off, turned towards mid-on for a single
a flighted delivery on middle and off, a lot of confused calling after White defends towards point
Miller's fantastic spell continues, White waits on the backfoot after seeing the ball pitch on middle and leg, turns across his bat and knocks back off stump
full delivery pitching outside off, driven confidently towards long-off for a single
a quick single is taken, Hopes blocks a short ball towards the off side
yorker on off, Ferguson digs it out towards the bowler
Ferguson is gone, a back of length ball outside off, Ferguson drives away from his body, gets an inside edge onto leg stump, "What mismatch," say the Windies
Johnson clips his first ball behind square leg for a single
full ball, defended back towards the bowler
length ball, pitching just outside off, driven confidently towards cover
Johnson gets forward and steers the ball towards backward point
length ball outside off, driven down to long-off
blocked back down the pitch
slightly ovepitched, just outside off, punched to long-on
defended stoutly off the front foot by Hopes
walks across the stumps and tucks a middle and off delivery behind square leg
back of a length on offstump, Hopes gets behind the line and blocks it back towards the bowler
angling into middle this time, turned towards midwicket
on the good length spot outside off, Hopes taps it to short cover
length ball heading for offstump, Hopes again jumps across the stumps and flicks it to midwicket, a good stop from the fielder there
appeal for caught behind, Johnson goes for a footwork-free drive outside the off, doesn't seem to have got an edge on that
Sammy ends an accurate over with a length ball on offstump, Johnson defends off the back foot
full ball outside off, eased towards long-on
Johnson stands tall and defends the ball back to the bowler
on middle stump, again Johnson pats it back to the bowler
this one doesn't turn after pitching outside off, Johnson is beaten after playing inside the line
Johnson turns that one to square leg, can't beat the fielder
inside-edge towards square leg to end the over
Sammy keeps nagging away around off stump, Hopes pats it back down the pitch

a beauty from Sammy ends Hopes' stay, holding its line after pitching on the back of a length outside off, Hopes closed the face of the bat, looking to play to the leg side, kisses the ball through to the keeper
Lee defends his first ball off the back foot
length ball just outside off, driven to long-off
length ball outside off, left alone by Johnson
another good ball to end the over, Johnson taps the offstump ball towards cover
a bit of turn after pitching on middle and leg, defended off the back foot
blocked back to the bowler by Lee
Lee offers the forward press as Miller keeps it tight
Lee guides this one towards backward point, Australia pinch a tight single
Johnson stands tall to drive, gets an outside edge towards short third man
ends with 10-1-24-2, finishes with a ball he has bowled all day today, pitching on a length, on offstump, Lee defends
Johnson feels for that one outside the off stump, doesn't make contact
on legstump, Johnson wanted to turn that to the leg side, closed the face too early, flies off the back of the bat towards backward point
length ball on middle and leg, Lee gets well forward and defends towards the bowler
a slower ball from Bernard, Lee is again content to defend back down the pitch
overpitched and well outside off, Lee takes a big backlift as if to drive powerfully, but there's no great power as he pushes it towards extra cover
Johnson carves it to backward point, wanted a single but is sent back
Tonge's first ball is in the channel just outside off, played towards third man
it may be a left-hand batsman this time, but Tonge isn't going to let go of hisback of length offstump line, defended towards the off side
worked away towards square leg for a quick couple
a massive, massive appeal for caught behind, Johnson goes for a big drive, gets an outside edge to the keeper, not given by the umpire
a low full toss is driven towards extra cover for two
an imperious pull from Johnson, no one is stopping that one
full and wide, Lee goes for the booming drive, doesn't make contact with the ball
back of length outside off, Lee carves it behind backward point
low full toss, Johnson muscles it down to long-on
wonderful shot from Lee, rocks back and clobbers a slower legcutter from Bernard in front of point
rapped on the gloves as Lee looks to defend off the back foot, the ball rolls towards the leg side
another low full toss, again Johnson gives long-on some work to do
first ball is powered away past point for four, Johnson rocks back and slaps that back of length delivery
another firm drive, this time to a full, wide ball, straight at extra cover
full and very wide, Johnson chase s after it but can't reach it
lovely swing of the bat from Johnson, gets under that length ball, doesn't quite get the distance as he sends it over the bowler's head, long-off runsacroos to field
short of length and just outside off, Johnson swats that with disdain into the grass banks beyond midwicket
this is even better, the fans lazing behind the midwicket boundary are being kept on their toes now, this was a flat hit, all power
this time he swings it over backward point, lands shirt of the boundary at cover point, gets a couple
low full toss outside off, bottom edged towards midwicket
back of a length ball on off, Johnson goes for the pull, but this was too quick for him, 146kmh, mistimes it to midwicket
slower ball from Roach, 106kmh (40kmh less than the previous one), full and outside off, Lee hits it back to the bowler
Lee swipes this one to midwicket for a single
back of a length and heading for Johnson's ribs, swung towards square leg
length ball slipping down leg, Lee backs away and punches the ball towards cover
low full toss outside off, carved towards cover for a single
full and wide outside off, Johnson backs away to crash it through the off side, but he misses
full toss outside off, Johnson gets it away towards sweeper cover for a single to bring up the 50 partnership
a near yorker on middle and leg, Lee muscle it to long-off for a single
another low full toss, this time on offstump, Johnson walks across and flicks it beautifully behind square

again Tonge keeps it full and outside off, Johnson sashays down the pitch to try hammer it to long-on, inside-edges it past the keeper for a boundary to fine leg, and this is now Johnson's highest ODI score
yet another full toss outside off, Lee throws his bat at it, doesn't get hold of it, but enough on it to carry beyond extra cover
a slower ball gone completely wrong,  he bowls the back-of-the-hand version, it was very high and very wide outside off, called a no-ball for height
Lee gets under this one and swings it over point for a couple
quick, short ball, Lee goes for the pull, top edges it over the keeper, runs coming in a hurry for Australia

chance of a run-out, Lee plays the ball back towards the bowler and sets off for a suicidal run, Roach gets to the ball quickly but can't hit the stumps at the keeper's end with Lee well short of his ground
Lee goes for an almighty heave to a back of length ball on middle stump, doesn't connect

Lee's run out this time, another slower ball, full and wide, Lee mishits it towards short third man, the keeper gets to the ball and throws it to the striker's end, Lee is out of his crease after being sent back by Johnson while going for the third
swing and a miss from Johnson
Johnson gets to his fifty with another boundary, a length ball is swung away past square leg
Johnson celebrates reaching the milestone with an effortless swipe to deposit the slower ball over midwicket, his third six in that region
a clean swing of the bat sends the ball towards long-off, doesn't time it well enough to get a boundary
that's a no-ball, full ball on the pads, Johnson carts that to the square leg boundary, and there's a free-hit for him as well
Johnson's going ballistic, he steps away and mows that one towards midwicket, doesn't carry all the way this time but he gets four runs
When it rains, it pours, a length ball on the pads is clipped past fine leg for a boundary
and a misfield this time, a length ball on off, Hauritz backs away and powers it towards extra cover who doesn't collect cleanly
full toss on middle, Hauritz backs away and swipes at it, bottom edged towards midwicket
length ball on the pads, Johnson smashes it towards midwicket, Johnson sprints back for a second
Johnson moved away from the stumps, Sammy sent that wide of the offstump, Johnson can't reach it, a welcome dot ball for the Windies
a powerful scythe over cover ends the inning, one bounce and over the rope. what a way to finish

inn2.comm: great start for the West Indies, Smith times a shortish ball past point for a boundary
two boundaries in two, on the pads, flicked fine past the keeper
chopped this one hard towards the keeper, Hussey leaps to latch on to that one
length ball just outside off, pushed towards extra cover for a single
well down the leg side, poor start from Lee
better from Lee, pitching back of a length on middle and off, nudged towards fine leg
fullish ball on offstump, punched towards cover, too firmly to have time for a single
Fletcher walks across and flicks Siddle's first ball towards square leg
length ball, struck on the thigh pad just outside off stump
this time it's on middle, again Fletcher can't get bat on it, struck high on middle stump
huge appeal from Siddle, this one was slightly fuller, and strikes the pads, above the knee roll and perhaps just outside off as well
puts bat on ball this time, tapped towards the leg side off the back foot
shuffles across and tries to swing it behind square, hit on the thigh pad and the ball bobbles towards square leg
short of length ball outside off, Fletcher looks to drive through the off and is beaten
Lee hurls this on off and middle, Fletcher gets behind the line and pushes it towards mid-on
Smith is hit on the pad this time, just outside leg stump, the ball dribbles towards midwicket
149.7 kmh from Lee, again Fletcher is beaten, he goes for a loose waft outside off and misses the ball
150.6 kmh this time, impressive pace but the line isn't, too far outside off
Lee keeps upping the pace here, this one is 151.8kmh, Fletcher is again beaten outside off as he looks to drive through the covers
150.5 kmh, length ball on off stump, Fletcher blocks it towards midwicket
a roundhouse cut from Smith sends that Siddle offering flying to the point boundary
length delivery angled across the batsman, Devon Smith goes for a cut, beaten
jags into the batsman after pitching on a length, Smith is cramped as he looks to cut, defends it
angling across Smith, who chases after it but misses
length ball on middle, Smith gets forward and blocks it back towards the bowler
another wide from Lee, this time down the leg side
again it's heading down leg, brushes Fletcher's pads on the way to the fine leg boundary
149.5kmh, better from Lee, length ball on offstump, Fletcher blocks on the front foot
Lee sends down a quick bouncer, 150.8 kmh, Fletcher sways and defends from the crease, Lee has some words for the batsman after that ball
151kmh, fullish and outside off, Fletcher again goes for the cover drive, inside edge sends the ball behind square leg
151.6 kmh, length ball in the corridor outside off, Fletcher lets it through to the keeper
Lee may be quick but it isn't helping him or Australia right now, this time is picked up from offstump and flicked over midwicket for four, a couple of bounces before it  reaches the rope
Smith has been fantastic with the cut today, and another fierce hit over point gets him four more, Hussey dives at point but can't get a hand on it
Siddle sends it full this time, Smith responds with a beautiful straight drive, last shot was all power this was all timing
Smith's is beaten by this one, looking to drive past extra cover, but doesn't connect
the bouncer does the trick for Siddle, Smith prods unconvincingly at it, edges it through to the keeper
length ball on middle and leg, thick inside edge onto the batsman's pads
fullish and just outside off, driven towards cover by Dowlin
yorker outside off, dug out towards the off side
Fletcher confidently punches that wide of mid-on, not too well timed so the fielder can pull it in just short of the ropes
Dowlin shoulders arms to a length delivery close to the offstump, 147kmh
149.7kmh, Dowlin doesn't bother with the footwork as he chase as a short ball just outside off, nearly edges it to the keeper
149 kmh, yorker just outside off, squeezed towards cover by Dowlin
that should get the confidence going for Dowlin, he gets forward and drives a 150kmh delivery past extra cover for four, well timed shot that
Fletcher shuffles across to try nudge an offstump ball towards the leg side, is hit high on the pads and the ball rolls towards midwicket

Dowlin looks to defends off the front foot, extra bounce has the ball hitting Dowlin on the gloves, the ball loops towards backward square leg, where Hussey fields and throws down the stumps at the striker's end
stands tall and defends towards the off side
shaping away after pitching back of a length, started well outside off, Fletcher looks to cut but misses
back of length ball in the channel outside off, had Fletcher feeling for it, beats the batsman
Shot! this time the ball is just outside off, Fletcher swings it straight over the bowler's head, just one bounce a few yards inside the rope
starts with a snorter that jumps from just back of a length, Dowlin jumps and defends awkwardly
half-volley well outside off, Dowlin bends his knee and cracks it past cover for four
another bouncer from Johnson, Dowlin jumps and defends again, not exactly in control of that one
angling across the batsman, who shoulders arms to that one
145kmh, length ball on the pads, tucked towards midwicket, 'No, no, no' Dowlin says when Fletcher calls for a run
length ball angling across the batsman, who defends with a flat bat, bottom edges towards his feet
a bouncer at 143 kmh, the batsman spots it early and ducks under it
another bouncer, 142.6 kmh, again Fletcher gets under it fairly easily
pitches it up this time, Fletcher plays it with an open face off the front foot, the ball squirts away towards third man
good ball from Siddle, on a length homing into off, blocked off the back foot
every now and then there has been a superb stroke from the West Indians, this was short of length, at least two feet outside off, Fletcher flatbats it over mid-on for a boundary
Siddle extracts some extra bounce, the ball strikes near the shoulder of the bat as Fletcher looks to defend
short and wide, left alone by the batsman
Fletcher jumps and looks to clip it to square leg, can't ride the bounce though and is hit on the glove, manages to keep it down though
Johnson lost his radar there, that would have been a wide outside off even in Tests
on the legstump, Dowlin gets on his toes and clips it to fine leg for an easy single
length ball heading for off, Fletcher defends back towards the bowler
short ball on middle, Fletcher manages to defend it towards square leg
well outside off, Dowlin is content to leave that one alone
Fletcher is squared up by Watson's first ball, he feels for it outside of and is beaten
gets forward and defends towards the covers
short ball on the leg stump, swung towards fine leg for a single
short of length, just outside off, blocked off the backfoot
a bit of width for Dowlin to work with, he goes for the cut, and misses the ball
Dowlin drops it towards backward point with soft hands and wants a quick single, but Fletcher sends him back
shortish ball, played on the up towards mid-off
Dowlin is struck in the armpit as he looks to defend a short ball
full and well outside off, left alone by the batsman
length ball, tipped towards backward point, Dowlin takes off the single, then screams 'no, no, no' to send Fletcher back
on the pads, clipped behind square leg for a single
Johnson finishes with a quick delivery, 150.5kmh, angling across the batsman, who shoulders arms
Watson slips in a bouncer, Dowlin looks to pull but decides against it
length ball just outside off, Dowlin shoulders arms, good carry through to the keeper
lovely shot off the back foot, caresses it off the thigh pad past mid-on for a couple
this shot fetches Dowlin double the runs, but he had no control over it, an inside edge past the keeper
much more solid this time, keeps bat and pad together as he defends towards cover
a short ball outside off to finish, Dowlin jumps to get on top of the bounce and defends
slightly overpitched outside off, Fletcher drives it over cover for a boundary
slower ball outside off, 128kmh, Fletcher shoulders arms
angling across the batsman, left alone outside off
sharp bouncer, the batsman just about manages to get his bat to ball to defend it in front of his face
shuffles across the stumps, gets an inside edge as he looks to work it to the leg side
again he walks across the stump, again he gets an inside edge onto his pads, this time the ball rolls towards square leg for a single
absolutely clubbed over midwicket, short of length ball, Fletcher gets his front foot out of the way and powers it for six
on leg stump this time, turned towards square leg
good running from the Windies, inside-edge onto the pads, the ball dribbles towards the keeper, Fletcher called for the run and set off immediately
goes to defend off the front foot but is beaten, a stifled appeal for caught behind
overpitched outside off, driven towards mid-off, not hit too firmly, so there was time for a single
lovely shot to bring up the fifty stand, shuffles across and hammers the ball from off stump past square leg
Fletcher looked to repeat that massive swipe over midwicket, this time he doesn't quite get hold of it ad it runs away to deep backward square leg
well outside off and the batsman shoulders arms
angling across the batsman, who is again happy to leave the ball
pushed towards covers off the front foot
shortish ball on the pads, awkwardly turned towards midwicket
short of length on middle stump, the batsman walks across and flicks the ball towards fine leg
back of a length heading for offstump, blocked back to the bowler
full ball on offstump, dug out towards cover
again a middle stump ball is clipped to fine leg for a single
nicely dabbed from outside off towards third man for a single
good running there, a slower ball, the batsman just drops it at his feet and calls for the run
full and outside off, crunched to sweeper cover for a single
overpitched outside off, swiped to long-on for a single
slightly shorter this time, pushed towards point
on the pads, turned towards short fine leg
no single again as short fine leg is called on to do more work
looks to sweep a full ball outside off, is hit on the gloves and the ball runs away to square leg
a tight over from Hauritz to start, last ball defended towards mid-on
length ball, around off, dabbed to wide of slip for one, 100 up
almost an edge, draws him into a shot outside off, and this one holds its line and beats him
walks across the stumps and flicks this one from in front of middle and gets one to long leg
back of a length, looks to tuck him up, e gets tall and gets a single to square leg
angling down the legs, misses out on a four, and what's more he has been denied the one leg bye. Tony Hill definitely got it wrong; he was looking to glance it and missed
flicks it from in front of stumps for one to midwicket
drives this down to long for one
slightly shorter, outside off, looks to late-cut but can't beat short third
stretches forwards, nudges it to wide of cover and comes through for one
big backswing, plays across the line, but manages to keep it along the ground
almost a return catch, short ball, looks to cut but this one stops on him, but the mis-hit falls just short of Hauritz
again he is early into the shot, looking to turn it to leg, but plays in the air and luckily for him it falls short of short midwicket
Hopes starts with a full ball on middle and leg, eased to the right of long-on for a single
short and wide, left alone by Dowlin
deftly dabs a ball from just outside off to third man for a single
another easy single, this time the batsman flicks behind square leg
single but a tight one this time, poked towards point where Hauritz was quickly onto the ball, no direct hit and the batsmen are home
works it away to midwicket for yet another single
punched down to long-on for a single
knocks it down to long-on for a single
gets forward and defends stoutly
eased to long-on for a single that brings up Fletcher's fifty
turned wide of short midwicket for another single
back of length outside off stump, sensibly eased to long-on for a single, no risks at all from these batsman
a wristy flick takes the ball from outside off to midwicket
another single, this time to deep backward square leg, tucked of the back foot
fullish ball on offstump, driven past the bowler, mid-off comes around to do the fielding
poked towards point for another single
glided to third man for the 19th consecutive single
make that 20, and the sixth of the over, toward square leg
starts with a sharp bouncer outside off, the batsman sways out of the way
jumps and plays this short ball with an angled bat past a diving backward point
extra bounce for Lee, the batsman looks to cut the short ball but is beaten by the sharply rising delivery

Johnson does the trick, he can't do anything wrong today, can he? Fletcher nearly holes out towards extra cover, it lands short but in attempting a quick run Fletcher is caught short, the direct hit finds him a yard out
a 148.2kmh delivery, length ball on off, awkwardly defended towards the off side
Dowlin reaches out to drive a full ball through cover, gets a thick outside edge which evades the wide slip but is fine enough to beat third man
Lee responds like a typical fast bowler, a quick bouncer which the batsman ducks under, that was 149kmh
Walton keeps bat and pad together as he stoutly defends towards the bowler
Walton's horror run with the bat continues, attempts a horrible across-the-line slog, inside-edges it onto the stumps
length ball pitching wide outside off and angling further away
Reifer lunges forward and defends a length ball towards mid-off
back of length and close to offstump, Reifer shoulders arms
and again, Reifer decides to not mess with a delivery angling across him
148.7kmh bouncer, too high for the umpire's liking
length ball on off, prodded towards point
pushed on the front foot towards cover point
on a length, heading for middle and off, turned towards midwicket for a single
Reifer gets well behind the line and blocks Lee back to the bowler
almost a replay of the previous ball, another dot ball
three in a row, Reifer jumps across his stumps and shows us his defensive technique
length ball on off, Dowlin lunges forward to defend, inside-edged towards square leg
slightly overpitched on middle stump, Reifer is content to block it back to the bowler
back of a length, a bit of width for Reifer, he gets an outside edge past slip for a boundary to third man
short of length, just outside off, Reifer jabs it towards square leg for a quick single
Hopes keeps it tight around off, tucked towards square leg for a single
Reifer reaches across and defends towards cover
eased down to long-on for a single by Reifer
Reifer showing some intent, sashays down the pitch and whips Hauritz wide of mid-on, Lee throws himself full-length to stop that
squeezed to short fine leg for a tight single
a paddle-sweep sends the ball fine past the keeper
nicely fielded by Hauritz, Dowlin punched that back towards the bowler, who moved quickly to his right to cut it off
flighted delivery, Dowlin looks to drive, he gets an inside edge onto his pads
Reifer gets well behind the line and defends back towards the bowler
another dot ball as Refier pokes the ball towards cover
this time Reifer gets it in the gap between cover and point for a single
Dowlin looks to flicks the ball off the backfoot towards midwicket, is struck high on the pads
length ball angling down leg, tipped towards square leg
Hopes slips in a legstump bouncer, Reifer goes for the pull, misses, the umpire says the ball is too high
full delivery on middle and off, pushed to mid-on
on the pads, flicked towards square leg for a single
Reifer gets a big stride in and defends towards the off side
this time Reifer gets his front foot across and blocks to the leg side for a single
on the pads, jabbed towards mid-on
Hauritz keeps the legstump line, pushed towards square leg
Reifer waltzes down the pitch, looking to whip it to midwicket, misses and is hit on the pads
starts with a back of a length ball on middle and leg, clipped towards midwicket for a single
back of a length again, just outside off, chopped towards point off the backfoot
short and wide, Reifer goes for a flamboyant cut, but fails to connect with the ball
Johnson, as he does so often, sends down a wild delivery, way down the leg side
shortish ball just outside off, Reifer prods it towards point and thinks of a single but decides against it
Reifer helps himself to another boundary to third man, he was looking to slash that hard past point, but gets a top edge past slip for four
full and on the pads, Reifer looks to glance that one but misses, the ball brushes the pads outside leg stump and runs away for four more
Dowlin reaches his half-century by lashing the ball to long-on for a single
cautiously defended back to the bowler
Reifer takes a couple of paces out of the crease as he defends
on middle and off, defended to short midwicket
Reifer again defends after taking a couple of steps down the track
on the pads, swept down to deep backward square lg by Reifer for a single to retain strike
Refier misses out on a low full toss outside off, muscling it to mid-on
another bouncer from Johnson, too high again
length ball, swinging into offstump, inside edged towards fine leg
back of a length ball that jags back into the right hander, Dowlin defends to the off side
angled across, left alone to the keeper
full and heading for middle, inside edged onto the pad
Reifer gets a single by whipping the ball towards mid-on
length ball, pitching just outside off, eased down to long-on
great fielding from Hopes ,Reifer turned to towards short cover, where Hopes dived to his right to cut that off
overpitched, Dowlin calmly punches it to long-on for another single
Reifer again jumps out of his crease, and defends to the bowler
length ball angling into the pads, turned towards mid-on
short and wide, Dowlin goes for a flamboyant cut but misses
good looking shot from Dowlin, carves a length ball to sweeper cover, there's a direct hit from the deep, Reifer was in though
another swing and a miss to a delivery outside off
dabs a wide ball behind backward point for a single
length ball on the pads, whipped behind square for a single
ooh, Reifer is beaten by the pace, struck on the pads, but very high on the pads, no chance of being out lbw
Dowlin mistimes an almighty heave from outside off to mid-on
full and very wide outside off, Lee is lucky that isn't deemed illegal

Tim Paine takes a superb catch, that spells the end of Dowlin, he went for a pull against a quick bouncer, gets a top edge and Paine had plenty of ground to cover before taking that catch, he raced back and finally took the catch diving on the sponsor's logo

that was a corker from Reifer, speed gun says 147 kmh but looked quicker, Reifer was thoroughly beaten for pace by that length delivery, Paine has a hard time collect that ball as it continues to rise till it reaches him
follows that up with a bouncer down the leg side, which is too wide for Paine to gather
length ball on middle and off, inside edged towards square leg, Reifer was looking to get that towards extra cover
back of a length delivery on the middle and leg, Reifer mistimes it to square leg
Siddle can't believe that one isn't lbw, Reifer was struck in front of middle but it pitched outside leg
bouncer is played with soft hands towards backward point
on a length, again Reifer is struck on the pads, this time just outside leg
Siddle switches to an outside-off line, edged down to third man for a single
Siddle slips in a bouncer, Bernard goes for the pull, gets a top edge which flies over slip, one bounce into the hoarding
Reifer goes for the pull but misses the ball, is struck on the pads outside off
length ball on off, Reifer swings it towards mid-on off the backfoot
length ball on middle and off, turned behind square leg, misfield by Watson allows the batsmen to come back for two
again a West Indian batsman can't connect with the ball, not even a top-edge this time
low full toss on off, punched to mid-on for a single
once again a pull is attempted, no contact is made, it's Reifer this time, the ball sails through to the keeper
Siddle hits middle, full and straight, Bernard backed away to try slash it through the off side, he misses, middle stump is rocked back
Sammy blocks his first ball watchfully back to the bowler
Sammy wafts at the ball outside off, doesn't connect
on the pads, Sammy punches it towards mid-on
Sammy defends as Siddle targets offstump, it was a back of a length, Sammy gets across and blocks back to the bowler
a bit of room for Sammy, and he crashes the ball over point for a boundary, wonderful shot, West Indies are going to need a fair few of those
length ball outside off, swung to wide mid-on by Reifer
superb delivery from Hopes, back of a length and moves slightly away from Sammy, who is beaten outside off
short and wide, Sammy swings at it and misses again
length ball on the pads, Sammy taps it to mid-on for a single
Reifer isn't doing his team any favours here, he looks to swipe that to midwikcte but edges onto the pads
finally, Reifer advances down the pitch and lofts a length ball on the pads over mid-on
length ball on middle and off, Sammy mistimes it in the air towards mid-off, lands short
well outside off, Sammy swings at it but misses
beautiful shot from Sammy, one of the best of the match, a length ball just outside off, powered over long-off
and again, Sammy is making a match of this, short of length on middle and off, carted over midwicket for another six
bouncer on leg stump this time, Sammy ducks under it
a repeat of the previous delivery, another bouncer at the body which Sammy can only bend under
Reifer gets forward and pushes the ball towards cover for a single to give Sammy the strike
short and wide, Sammy leaves it thinking it will be a wide, the crowd starts screaming expecting a wide, Asad Rauf doesn't think it is, and he's probably right
Sammy goes for a flamboyant heave to a ball outside off, misses the ball
full ball just outside off, Sammy tries to force it through the off side but the ball sneaks between bat and pad
another everything-behind-it heave to an outside off ball, Sammy doesn't make contact again
Watson completes a fantastic over for Australia with a yorker length delivery way outside off, Sammy can't get bat on ball again
now it's Reifer's turn to fail to connect with the ball, misses a ball angling across him
back of length delivery outside off, Reifer tries to tickle it to third man but misses
length ball on legstump, Reifer mistimes the ball towards midwicket, lands a few yard short of the fielder

Sammy gets under a wide ball and it sails towards Ferguson at third man, reaches him on the bounce, Ferguson can't pick it up cleanly, juggles with the ball a couple of times, and just about keeps it inside the rope
length ball on legstump this time, Sammy can't get that away
terrific yorker to end the over, heading for legstump, Sammy does well to get some bat on it, squeezing it to the off side

a high full toss does the job for Australia, Sammy absolutely hammers that, but straight to Hussey at sweeper cover, he really blasted that one, pity about the placement, the umpires discuss whether that full toss was above waist high, they decide it's okay, Sammy's got to go
Nikita Miller carves his first ball to point
a full ball ion leg stump, Miller eases it inside-out towards long-off
another high full toss, this was over waist high, Reifer slams it to midwicket, Watson gets one warning for dangerous bowling
Miller slashes this one to third man for a single
a full ball just outside off, Reifer looks to crash that over mid-off, only gets it to point, where Hauritz accepts an easy catch
Roach strokes his first ball beautifully past cover, Hussey at sweeper cover does the fielding
back of a length just outside off, pushed towards backward point, 'Nooooo' is the call
a sharp bouncer from Johnson, Roach can't get bat on it
full ball just outside off, Roach opens the face to get the ball towards backward point, again no run
Johnson sends one angling across Roach, just outside off, Roach is beaten
a bouncer over Roach's head, too high
Roach shuffles across and glides the ball behind square leg for a single
slightly overpitched outside off, Miller looks to drive, gets a inside edge, the ball dribbles towards the keeper
the batsman looks to cut but misses the ball
cut away to deep point for a single
pushed to mid-on for a single
Hauritz strikes, Miller looks to swipe the ball beyond midwicket, a top edge sends the ball towards Ponting at midwicket, simple catch
another wicket for Hauritz, Roach swings the bat at a ball outside off, edges it towards Johnson at short third man
